article.headline: Old Dominion 86, Towson 56
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Gerald Lee scored 17 points to lead Old Dominion to an 86-56 rout over Towson on Saturday in the quarterfinals of the Colonial Athletic Association tournament. The top-seeded Monarchs (24-8) advance to Sunday's semifinals to face the winner of the Virginia Commonwealth-George Mason game. Six different Monarchs scored during a 13-3 spurt early in the first half. The eighth-seeded Tigers (9-21) were held to one field goal over 6:42 as Old Dominion took a 17-10 lead with 10:33 left. A 12-1 run over the final 4:07 of the half gave the Monarchs a 39-21 halftime lead. Old Dominion held Towson to 30.8 percent from the floor and outrebounded the Tigers 28-11 -- 13 offensive boards. Old Dominion hit its first seven field goals in the second half. Lee?s nine points sparked a 20-9 start for the Monarchs. The biggest lead for Old Dominion was 80-43 with 6:39 left.
